{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"d52ccd08-921c-46ff-974e-b50f86220e43","content":"Created `.github/workflows/publish.yml`. Here's how it works:\n\n| Piece | Purpose |\n|---|---|\n| `id-token: write` | Lets GitHub mint an OIDC token for the workflow run |\n| `environment: nuget` | Must match what you registered on nuget.org (also adds approval gates) |\n| `nuget/publish@v1` | Exchanges the OIDC token with nuget.org — no API key needed |\n| Tag trigger (`v*`) | Push `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags` to publish |\n\n## 3. Recommended: set the version from the tag\n\nAdd this to your `.csproj` or pass it during pack:\n\n```xml\n<!-- src/MyLib/MyLib.csproj -->\n<PropertyGroup>\n  <PackageId>MyOrg.MyLib</PackageId>\n  <VersionPrefix>1.0.0</VersionPrefix>\n</PropertyGroup>\n```\n\nThen override at build time:\n\n```yaml\n- run: |\n    VERSION=${GITHUB_REF_NAME#v}\n    dotnet pack src/MyLib/MyLib.csproj -c Release -o ./artifacts -p:Version=$VERSION\n```\n\n**To publish:** create a GitHub environment called `nuget` (Settings → Environments), then `git tag v1.0.0 && git push --tags`.","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"e93e9974-5b1a-4a0b-a2f1-a35fa05f8a20","outputTokens":332,"requestId":"FE04:2A7C5F:139D48F:15F111C:6A066E9C"},"id":"2962cc82-40e9-4ccf-8328-535282dd4ebf","timestamp":"2026-05-15T00:53:56.194Z","parentId":"381c1620-3da4-4926-83d3-b8feb73cc66c"}
